Global Test 
Table 1 shows the results of GRP-FED and baselines on both real-world MIT-BIH and synthesis CIFAR-10 datasets. The global test (Tgsubscript𝑇𝑔T_{g}) is to evaluate the fairness of the global model over the entire testing set. It shows that our GRP-FED achieves the highest macro-F1 score on both MIT-BIH (56.9%percent56.956.9\%) and CIFAR-10 (57.8%percent57.857.8\%). Since the proposed adaptive aggregation adjusts the power of loss according to the dynamic fairness, it gains a significant improvement under Tgsubscript𝑇𝑔T_{g} and achieves better global fairness.
